last_episode_to_air.name: I Won't Leave You Alone
last_episode_to_air.overview: Culinary school's much harder than Deckard expected. But when he decides to quit and go home, his self-assured classmate insists on tagging along.

name: Bee and PuppyCat
overview: On a charming magical island, the impulsive Bee and her furry pal get up to all sorts of adventures while working for an intergalactic temp agency.

seasons.name: The Series
seasons.overview: Bee and PuppyCat meet and begin their adventures together.

seasons.name: Lazy in Space
seasons.overview: The beloved lead charactersâ€™ world is even more expansive (and possibly in danger) as the pair combat problems big, small, and totally weird, all while trying to make rent in time.

episodes.name: Food
episodes.overview: One morning Bee wakes from a dream and is starving. New recipe in hand Bee and PuppyCat head to the store and then to cook with Deckard.

episodes.name: Farmer
episodes.overview: After receiving a new assignment from TempBot, and in new uniforms (magic pockets included), Bee and PuppyCat slide into a farming job on Jelly Cube Planet.

episodes.name: Beach
episodes.overview: When Cardamon the cranky landlord kicks them out of the apartment, Bee and PuppyCat head to the beach and search for a place to watch the Pretty Patrick Lunchtime Marathon.

episodes.name: Cats
episodes.overview: Bee and PuppyCat travel to a bathhouse on Cat-Head Planet for their strangest and most adorable job yet. Lucky for them, Pretty Patrick is on TV over there, too!

episodes.name: Birthday
episodes.overview: It's Bee's birthday and PuppyCat offers to spend time with her, so she takes him to an abandoned arcade with games constructed by her father.

episodes.name: Game
episodes.overview: Bee's mood turns gleefully around when she and PuppyCat get assigned a job on Cloud World, an immersive video game inhabited by squat birds. When Bee's gender-swapped video game avatar gets wrapped in the glamour of side quests, it's up to PuppyCat to win the game and defeat the all-seeing eye of Cloud World.

episodes.name: Toast
episodes.overview: Rent is due! An old wrestling acquaintance comes to visit Cass.

episodes.name: Dogs
episodes.overview: Bee and Deckard go to pay rent to Cardamon. Cardamon wants PuppyCat to spend time with Sticky.

episodes.name: Wedding
episodes.overview: Cardamon wants to marry PuppyCat and Sticky.

episodes.name: Donut
episodes.overview: Bee and Deckard are given a baking temp job on Donut Planet. They make donuts until a black hole destroys the planet.

episodes.name: Again for the First Time
episodes.overview: Bee feels a little dejected when she's fired from her job, but then a cute little cat â€” or is it a dog? â€” falls out of the sky right onto her umbrella.

episodes.name: Who Would Want This?
episodes.overview: Tempbot has a lot of jobs lined up for Bee and PuppyCat today. First up, the duo heads over to Snowglobe Planet to repair a music box.

episodes.name: What Do You Want to Be?
episodes.overview: It's Bee's birthday! After she bumps into Deckard on her way to the arcade, they start hanging out â€” then they both get assigned to a new temp job.

episodes.name: Gentle Touch
episodes.overview: Deckard cashes in an IOU card he got from Bee by asking her to look after his family while he's away at culinary school.

episodes.name: Little Fingers
episodes.overview: Toast dramatically announces that she's pregnant. Bee asks Tempbot for a big job so she can pay for PuppyCat's out-of-control in-app purchases.

episodes.name: Day Off Work
episodes.overview: It's Cas's day off, and she has big plans. To start with, she puts on all the face masks she's been hoarding, totally creeping everyone out.

episodes.name: Snow and Violets
episodes.overview: Today's the day when the island goes through all four seasons, and Bee can't wait to catch every magical moment with PuppyCat.

episodes.name: Funny Lying
episodes.overview: On a beautiful sunny day, Bee, Cardamon and PuppyCat walk down to the beach, where PuppyCat gets into a scuffle with an old enemy.

episodes.name: My Favorite
episodes.overview: Pretty Patrick comes back from vacation with a baby... and a very snazzy beard. PuppyCat wants to go see him at the train station.

episodes.name: Did You Remember
episodes.overview: PuppyCat's been preparing for a special day for three whole months. Bee kindly helps Cardamon and Sticky reach the controls at the arcade.

episodes.name: Bird Friend
episodes.overview: PuppyCat's been extra mushy lately, and it's driving Bee nuts. She asks the smartest person she knows for help, but even Cas doesn't know what to do.

episodes.name: Two Clown Noses
episodes.overview: Cas and the family throw a surprise birthday party for Crispin, who's been through a lot. Later, he goes on an out-of-this-world date with Bee.

episodes.name: Golden Eyes
episodes.overview: For his birthday, Howell gets to eat cake in the morning â€” just how he likes it. PuppyCat really needs to go, so Bee asks for a job on Toilet Planet.

episodes.name: Why Don't You Help Me
episodes.overview: There are vines growing out of everyone's pipes, and it's really stressing Cardamon out since he's a landlord. He's also a very sleepy 7-year-old.
